  "text": "## Access Log Filter Implementations (source/common/access_log/)\n\nAll filter implementations are in `access_log_impl.h/.cc`. Filters are boolean evaluators (not loggers), so they do NOT produce text/JSON output. They are:\n- **ComparisonFilter** (base), **StatusCodeFilter**, **DurationFilter** \u2014 compare numeric values\n- **OperatorFilter** (base), **AndFilter**, **OrFilter** \u2014 boolean combinators\n- **NotHealthCheckFilter**, **TraceableRequestFilter**, **RuntimeFilter** \u2014 conditional filters\n- **HeaderFilter**, **ResponseFlagFilter**, **GrpcStatusFilter** \u2014 match on request/response properties\n- **LogTypeFilter**, **MetadataFilter** \u2014 match on access log type and dynamic metadata\n- **CELAccessLogExtensionFilter** (extensions/access_loggers/filters/cel/) \u2014 CEL expression-based extension filter\n\nFilters are NOT relevant to structured vs. unstructured logging; they only decide whether to log.\n\n## Access Log Sink Implementations (source/extensions/access_loggers/)\n\n### 1. File Access Logger (`envoy.access_loggers.file`)\n- **C++ impl**: `common/file_access_log_impl.h/.cc`, `file/config.cc`\n- **Proto**: `file/v3/file.proto` \u2014 `FileAccessLog`\n- **JSON support**: YES \u2014 supports `format` (text), `json_format` (JSON), `typed_json_format` (typed JSON), and `log_format` (SubstitutionFormatString, which supports both text and JSON). The config factory explicitly handles `kJsonFormat` and `kTypedJsonFormat` cases.\n\n### 2. Stdout/Stderr Access Loggers (`envoy.access_loggers.stdout`, `envoy.access_loggers.stderr`)\n- **C++ impl**: `stream/config.cc`, `common/stream_access_log_common_impl.h` (template), reuses `FileAccessLog`\n- **Proto**: `stream/v3/stream.proto` \u2014 `StdoutAccessLog`, `StderrAccessLog`\n- **JSON support**: YES \u2014 via `log_format` (SubstitutionFormatString) which supports `json_format` field.\n\n### 3. HTTP gRPC Access Logger (`envoy.access_loggers.http_grpc`)\n- **C++ impl**: `grpc/http_grpc_access_log_impl.h/.cc`, `grpc/http_config.cc`\n- **Proto**: `grpc/v3/als.proto` \u2014 `HttpGrpcAccessLogConfig`\n- **JSON support**: Neither text nor JSON \u2014 uses protobuf-structured `StreamAccessLogsMessage.http_logs` (proto-binary/gRPC). The output is always structured protobuf, not text or JSON.\n\n### 4. TCP gRPC Access Logger (`envoy.access_loggers.tcp_grpc`)\n- **C++ impl**: `grpc/tcp_grpc_access_log_impl.h/.cc`, `grpc/tcp_config.cc`\n- **Proto**: `grpc/v3/als.proto` \u2014 `TcpGrpcAccessLogConfig`\n- **JSON support**: Neither text nor JSON \u2014 uses structured protobuf via gRPC ALS, same as HTTP gRPC.\n\n### 5. OpenTelemetry Access Logger (`envoy.access_loggers.open_telemetry`)\n- **C++ impl**: `open_telemetry/access_log_impl.h/.cc`, `open_telemetry/grpc_access_log_impl.h/.cc`, `open_telemetry/substitution_formatter.h/.cc`, `open_telemetry/config.cc`\n- **Proto**: `open_telemetry/v3/logs_service.proto` \u2014 `OpenTelemetryAccessLogConfig`\n- **JSON support**: Structured (but not JSON) \u2014 uses OpenTelemetry protobuf `KeyValueList` for body and attributes. The `OpenTelemetryFormatter` converts substitution format patterns into OTLP `KeyValueList` structures. It supports structured key-value output natively via protobuf, not JSON text.\n\n### 6. Fluentd Access Logger (`envoy.access_loggers.fluentd`)\n- **C++ impl**: `fluentd/fluentd_access_log_impl.h/.cc`, `fluentd/substitution_formatter.h/.cc`, `fluentd/config.cc`\n- **Proto**: `fluentd/v3/fluentd.proto` \u2014 `FluentdAccessLogConfig`\n- **JSON support**: YES (internally structured) \u2014 the `record` field is a `google.protobuf.Struct` (JSON-like map). `FluentdFormatterImpl` wraps a JSON formatter and converts its output to MessagePack. So the input is JSON-structured, serialized to msgpack for Fluentd protocol.\n\n### 7. Wasm Access Logger (`envoy.access_loggers.wasm`)\n- **C++ impl**: `wasm/wasm_access_log_impl.h`, `wasm/config.h/.cc`\n- **Proto**: `wasm/v3/wasm.proto` \u2014 `WasmAccessLog`\n- **JSON support**: Depends on the WASM plugin \u2014 the Wasm access logger delegates to a WASM VM. The format is entirely determined by the loaded WASM module. It can potentially support any format.\n\n### Additional proto-only definitions (no matching C++ in source/extensions/access_loggers/):\n- `stats/v3/stats.proto` \u2014 `envoy.access_loggers.stats`: emits stats/counters/histograms, not text/JSON logging\n- `dynamic_modules/v3/dynamic_modules.proto` \u2014 `envoy.access_loggers.dynamic_modules`: delegates to dynamically loaded shared objects\n- `filters/process_ratelimit/v3/process_ratelimit.proto` \u2014 `envoy.access_loggers.extension_filters.process_ratelimit`: a rate-limiting filter, not a sink",
